  <summary date="2020-01-16T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Eyes on the Courts Act of 2020

This bill requires U.S. appellate courts to permit the photographing, recording, broadcasting, televising, or streaming&#160;of court proceedings unless the presiding judge determines&#160;that doing so&#160;would violate the due process rights of any party to the proceedings&#160;or is otherwise not in the interests of justice.</summary>
